title: For Sale:  Walther  P99 AS 9MM 2015
location: Traverse City, Northern Lower Peninsula, Michigan
postcontent: 2015 Walther P99AS 9mm. In Excellent condition; only 150 rounds through it. Comes with case, 2 magazines, 3 backstraps & assorted height front sights. This is the AS model, or "Anti-Stress" trigger designation, referring to the first trigger pull being Double Action at a long 9.5# pull, and all succeeding trigger pulls being a short, Very Crisp 4.5# pull, followed by a short, very tactile reset. There is a de-cocker on top of the slide to safely drop the trigger from Single Action, back to the Longer, safer Double Action. 4" barrel with polished feed ramp, and the Lever-style magazine release on either side of the trigger guard, which are actually easier to use than a standard magazine release button. This gun is VERY accurate in Single Action mode, and is a favorite of many military and police units around the world.       As such, the 9mm model is made primarily for those units, and are RARELY found in the U.S., unlike the .40 caliber models which are common here in the States.  This is the rare and very sought-after 9mm model, and is an excellent Example of Walther engineering. It is also the primary design that spawned the current PPQ model from Walther, that is getting rave reviews, but while the PPQ has a very light trigger & NO safety, the P99AS with DA/SA & decocker, and is very safe to carry loaded.      I'm an empty-nester now, and need to thin out the gun cabinet.    Bluebook on this 2-year old model is $485.00. But life has been good to me, and I just need to find it a good home, so I'll let it go for $400.00 + $30.00 shipping/handling from my FFL to your FFL.    That's a very good deal for this rare 9mm model with hardly any miles on it.
